<h2>Create a new Rails app</h2>
<p>
  To create the application, run the following command:
</p>

<pre><code class="ruby">
rails new filmster --skip-test-unit --database=postgresql --skip-turbolinks
</code></pre>

<p>
  There a few things that you have probably never seen before. 
</p>

<p>
  Since we are going to use RSpec to test our application, we are not going to use test unit. We can disable it by creating our Rails app with the <code>--skip-test-unit</code> option.
</p>

<p>
  Turbolinks makes our Rails applications quick and snappy. However, it introduces some difficulties when using JavaScript. A lot of developers are against using turbolinks in their applications because it causes a lot of unnecessary tradeoffs that make turbolinks not worth the hassle. In our app, we aren't going to need turbolinks since we are going to render a lot of things using Javascript, so let's turn it off. We can disable it with the <code>--skip-turbolinks</code> option.
</p>

