  Watch <%= link_to 'this', 'http://railscasts.com/episodes/390-turbolinks', target: '_blank' %> episode of Railscast for an overview of what Turbolinks is, the problems it introduces, and how to overcome them.
</p>

<h2>Disabling Generators</h2>

<p>
  You might have noticed in Ideator and Instapost that everytime we generate a new model or controller, a bunch of files are generated automatically, including CSS, JavaScript, and helper files that we don't need.
</p>

<p>
  A lot of times, these CSS and JavaScript files indeed do stay unused, and we end up having to delete them. However, we can disable the generation of these files by default.
</p>

<p>
  Open your <code>application.rb</code> file and add the following lines of code inside of the <code>Application</code> class.
</p>

<pre><code class="ruby">
config.generators do |g|
  generate.helper false
  generate.assets false
end
</code></pre>

<p>
  This piece of code will disable the automatic generation of these files that are usually unnecessary.
</p>

